Millennium Footbridge, England

Portfolios


BEC manages investment portfolios developed to meet the varying risk/return profiles of different investors. Each portfolio is constructed around a long-term strategic asset allocation strategy using a diverse basket of ETFs that provide targeted global exposure to equities, fixed income, and liquid alternative assets. Each portfolio is managed with the objective to maximize after-tax, after-fee investment returns while actively managing risk by using a tactical asset allocation approach to optimize exposure by asset class, geography, sector and market capitalization. All portfolios are managed by the BEC Investment Committee.
 


Global Equity

The BEC Global Equity Portfolio seeks long term capital appreciation by investing in a highly diversified basket of ETFs focused on equities and liquid alternative assets. The Portfolio invests 75-100% of assets in ETFs focused on large cap, mid cap, and small cap equities, both in the U.S. and in developed and emerging international markets. The Portfolio will also invest 0-15% of assets in ETFs focused on liquid alternative investments, including real estate, commodities, and master limited partnerships.



