Global Growth

The BEC Global Growth Portfolio seeks long term capital appreciation by investing in a highly diversified basket of ETFs focused on equities, fixed income, and liquid alternative assets. The Portfolio invests 60-90% of assets in ETFs focused on large cap, mid cap, and small cap equities, both in the U.S. and in developed and emerging international markets. The Portfolio also invests 10-30% of assets in ETFs focused on domestic and international fixed income and 0-15% in ETFs focused on liquid alternative investments, including real estate, commodities, inflation-protected securities, and master limited partnerships.



Domestic Equity
37%
International Equity
37%
Global Fixed Income
16%
Liquid Alternatives
