Number of primary asset classes
4
Number of sub-sectors
20
Number of individual holdings
20-40





Global Balanced

The BEC Global Balanced Portfolio seeks long term capital appreciation and current income by investing in a highly diversified basket of ETFs focused on equities, fixed income, and liquid alternative assets. The Portfolio invests 40-80% of assets in ETFs focused on large cap, mid cap, and small cap equities, both in the U.S. and in developed and emerging international markets. The Portfolio also invests 20-40% of assets in ETFs focused on domestic and international fixed income and 0-15% in ETFs focused on liquid alternative investments, including real estate, commodities, inflation-protected securities, and master limited partnerships.



Domestic Equity
30%
International Equity
30%
Global Fixed Income
