Liquid Alternatives
10%


Number of primary asset classes
4
Number of sub-sectors
20
Number of individual holdings
20-40





Global Growth and Income

The BEC Global Growth & Income Portfolio seeks current investment income with some long term capital appreciation by investing in a highly diversified basket of ETFs focused on fixed income, equities, and liquid alternative assets. The Portfolio typically invests 40-70% of assets in a diverse basket of ETFs focused on domestic and international fixed income securities. The Portfolio also provides the potential for long term capital growth through a 20-60% exposure to ETFs focused on large cap, mid cap, and small cap equities in the U.S. and in developed and emerging international markets and a 0-15% allocation to ETFs focused on liquid alternative investments, including real estate, commodities, inflation-protected securities, and master limited partnerships.



